        "content": {
          "title": "About Bitcoin (BTC)",
          "description": "Bitcoin (BTC) is the first cryptocurrency built on blockchain technology, also known as a decentralized digital currency that is based on cryptography. Unlike government-issued or fiat currencies such as US Dollars or Euro which are controlled by central banks, Bitcoin can operate without the need of a central authority like a central bank or a company.\u00a0The decentralized nature allows it to operate on a peer-to-peer network whereby users are able to send funds to each other without going through intermediaries."
        }
      }
